Alan Harlan

Mr. Harlan co-leads the North American Business Unit. He is responsible for general operations, growth and P&L management of EPAM’s US and Global customers in Healthcare & Life Sciences and Energy verticals.
Prior to EPAM, Mr. Harlan held a number of senior management roles in the Software Services and Outsourcing industries. Most recently, he served as CEO and a Member of the Board of SoftServe Inc., a US based Software Services Company with delivery operations in Ukraine, Bulgaria and Poland. Prior to that, Mr. Harlan was Executive Vice President & General Manager of the Software Product and Platform Division and President of the Software Management Solutions Division for Symphony Teleca Corp where he was responsible for over $200M in business and covered North America, Latin America, India, China, Western Europe, CIS, and Eastern Europe. Before that, he was with Affiliated Computer Services, a $2.6B Global IT Services Firm, with roles including Vice President Sales, SVP CTO and Divisional EVP.
Mr. Harlan holds a BA in Accounting and Finance from the Louisiana State University.






            Show Less
        

            Read More
        





Björn Brauel
Co-Head European Business






Björn Brauel
Co-Head European Business
Mr. Brauel leads EPAM’s business in continental Europe. He is responsible for general operations, growth and P&L management of EPAM’s business in Germany, Netherlands and Austria.
With more than 20 years of experience in software design and development, services delivery, management and business development Mr. Brauel always puts customer value first. His knowledge of technology combined with the ability to understand customer challenges and communicate and craft solutions for his customers are key to his leadership style.
In 1999 Mr. Brauel joined Software AG as an engineer working within the core product development group on new technologies. After having gone through roles in Product Marketing and Management, he spearheaded new and innovative service practices around solutions and transformation for the services group of Software AG and ran global sales and P&L for the services business of Software AG.
Mr.Brauel holds a computer science degree from the Technical University of Darmstadt.






            Show Less
        

            Read More
        





Solman Rahman
Co-Head European Business






Solman Rahman
Co-Head European Business
Mr. Rahman is Vice President and leads EPAM’s Northern Europe Business. He is responsible for business operations, growth and P&L management of EPAM’s UK, Ireland and Nordics business.
Mr. Rahman has extensive experience in delivering business growth, leading high-performance teams and managing highly profitable global client portfolios. Prior to joining EPAM in September 2013 Mr Rahman spent a decade at Cognizant, an industry leader where he was part of its European Leadership Team within its Strategic Engagements & High-Value Deals Unit. Previous to this he served as a Director for Getronics, a European SI in its Business Consulting Team.
Mr. Rahman started his career as an Analyst for Cowen & Company in its investment banking technology sector. He worked with early-stage and pre-IPO technology companies in equity underwriting and M&A advisory assignments.
Mr. Rahman holds a BSc in Economics from the LSE (University of London).






            Show Less
        

            Read More
        





Darren Starsmore
Head of APAC Business






Darren Starsmore
Head of APAC Business
Darren Starsmore is Managing Director for the Asia Pacific (APAC) region. He is responsible for business operations, delivery, growth and profitability for EPAM. He brings more than three decades of experience designing, developing and delivering technology solutions in a wide variety of industries, including Financial Services.
Prior to his role at EPAM, Mr. Starsmore spent more than ten years at UBS where he ran the Proprietary Electronic Trading Desk for the equity business before moving into senior IT roles within the Investment Bank and Wealth Management. He started his career as an electronics engineer in the medical systems industry, designing graphical processing hardware and software and worked in areas as diverse as airport weather systems, digital music mixing desks and video processing.
Mr. Starsmore holds a Higher National Certificate in Computer Technology from the University of Bedfordshire.






            Show Less
        

            Read More
        





Vasily Agafonov
Head of CIS Business






Vasily Agafonov
Head of CIS Business
Mr. Agafonov became General Manager of EPAM Systems Russia in March 2007 when VDI, a Russian software development company, where he served as COO, merged with EPAM Systems.
In his present position, Mr. Agafonov manages the EPAM business in the CIS region. He ensures the accomplishment of EPAM’s business goals, oversees planning and budgeting activities and executes performance analysis of CIS Operations.
A graduate from the Bauman Moscow State Technical University, Mr. Agafonov is an expert in the field of project management and quality management systems certification (CMMI/ISO 9001:2000).






